    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Hypericum olivieri are primarily focused on its medicinal properties, including the extraction of its active compounds such as hyperforin and hypericin. Hypericum oil is obtained through cold-pressing of the plant's leaves and flowers, rich in essential fatty acids and antioxidants. Hypericum tincture is a liquid extract of the plant, obtained through the use of solvents such as ethanol or glycerol, which is often used for its antidepressant and anti-inflammatory effects. Topical preparations like salve and infusion are also used for wound healing and skin issues, while the dried leaves and flowers can be made into a tea for its relaxing and calming properties. These preparations are used to take advantage of the plant's adaptogenic and anti-inflammatory properties, as well as its ability to stimulate the nervous system.",
